Title: Events in "any" state not properly handled.

This state machine:

SM
{
   *A [ event --> B, weird --> B ],
    B [ event --> A ],
    _ [ weird --> A ]
}


generates this code:

void SM_weird(const SM_weird_t *e)
{
    const char *event_name = "weird";

    SM_initialize();
    
    switch(SM_state) {
    case SM_A:
        SM_A_weird(e);
        break;
        
    case SM_B:
        SM_UNHANDLED_EVENT(event_name);
        break;
        
    default:
        SM_UNHANDLED_EVENT(event_name);
        break;
    }
}

but I would expect case SM_B to cause a state transition to A.
